The paper focuses on improving fine grained recognition accuracy using geolocation information, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses various ways of incorporating geolocation information, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the paper introduces two new datasets, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
